	Location location location	It has to be said again, the Paris has an outstanding location, right at center Strip. combine that with frequent rate deals and you have an excellent Vegas homebase. Access to the Bally's monorail station (but beware, you have to go though Bally's to get there, and man is that a long schlep!) and regular shuttles to the Rio keep it hooked up with many other properties.For a &quot;theme&quot; Strip hotel it's of human-manageable size and apart from the Eiffel Tower replica it does not contain all those extravagant attractions others seem to favor (zoos, gardens, water attractions, rides)As for its use as a hotel, per se, definitely a middle-of-the-road property. (Part of the Harrah's group). The high-floor rooms that got renovated/redecorated are now sold as &quot;upgraded&quot; &quot;Red Rooms&quot;&quot;, for a higher price. (and premium if you have an actual Strip view) Comfortable and well appointed but the bathroom did not quite get the attention you'd expect -- non-adjustable, cheap-looking showerheads, and the separate tub is small. A person could be well served with just the base room if they care nothing about decor or view.One hint to give: unless the intention is just to pig out, many senible people should opt out of the buffet -- pricey and very long lines -- and instead hit one of the standalone dining sites in the resort.	
Nov 25 2009 	Satisfied Overall	Great location on the strip. This resort is a good size - small enough that it's not as vast and impersonal as others on the strip, but large enough to offer a wide variety of restaurants and activities.Check-in had a long line and somewhat slow service - this could be a nightmare if arriving at a peak time. All the employees we encountered were very professional and friendly. Only exception was at JJ's Boulangerie - would not recommend it!The standard room was better than expected - not bad at all for the price. Even though we didn't upgrade to a &quot;Red Room,&quot; there was a big red stain across the carpet. I'm choosing to believe it was fruit punch. The bathroom was great, with a separate glass shower. Lots of hallway noise - much more than you'd expect from a newer building.This hotel is typically priced just above Luxor and NYNY, and would be worth the extra $10-15 per night to be closer to the center strip.	
