Oct 28 2009 	Great place to stay!	The location of this hotel is fabulous! It was a great place to stay, especially because this was my first trip to Vegas. Since Paris is centrally located you can walk to almost anything on the strip, and if you choose to take a cab the fare is rarely above $8. The room was a pretty standard hotel room, nothing fancy, but it probably exceeded my expectations for the price we paid. Very clean too! I really enjoyed the the theme and decor of the hotel even if it is a little kitschy (its vegas, what do you expect?!). It did not remind me at all of the real Paris, France, but it was cute nonetheless. Don't miss the creperie if you stay here, its great for breakfast! The casino itself is not that great for table games, so if you're a serious gambler, you may want to consider staying in another casino. But overall I have no complaints and I would defintely recommned Paris.	
