Sep 29 2009 	PAris Hotel WAY better than other reviews would led me to believe	I was terrified, just terrified to stay at this hotel after I read the reviews on this site; well, thankfully they were all wrong, all of them. We arrived for our conference at 11:00pm, there were no lines, the lobby was beautiful, sparklingly clean and the check in was easy. Paula, who works the night shift there, gave us a free upgrade to the most beautiful suite, it is larger than my NY apartment and reminded me of the old Plaza Hotel. The room was clean and lovely and had two bathrooms and a huge jacuzzi. The hotel halls were clean and well lit and the maid service was spectacular. We got turn down service and that was just sweet and lovely. The food in the hotel is just o.k. and the casino seems dark but we didn't gamble there so who cares. The pool was beautiful and the hotel is very quiet. I would stay at this hotel again, no question and I would recommend it to anyone. I don't know what these other people are going on about, really.	
