Sep 16 2009 	Second stay at the Paris it's ok not great.	The best part of this hotel is the location as most reviewers have pointed out. My wife and I recently stayed 5 days/ 4 nights from 9/7 - 9/11/09 to celebrate our anniversary; we spent 3 nights at this same hotel the year before. The hotel is nice, the service staff is somewhat friendly. I've found that the housekeeping staff to be much friendlier than the front desk. The rooms and hallways are showing some wear, but this isn't exactly the Four Seasons nor The Ritz Carlton.Lenotre is a cafe within the hotel which offeres pastries/sandwiches and coffee; however, just like the year before, the service line is slow just to get a cup of coffee. For some reason, the operation in this cafe just isn't the most efficient. If you don't need the immediate caffeine hit first thing in the morning and refuse to wait in line for at least 10 minutes, walk 5 minutes to the south where Planet Hollywood is located, there's a Starbucks there. Otherwise, we dined fairly casually throughout the strip. We spent the afternoons gambling at various hotel casinos up and down the strip. In the evening, we would return to the Paris and play the slots there. The payouts at the Paris was awful, I had much better luck at Planet Hollywood next door and at the New York New York.Walgreens and CVS is just 3 blocks south of the Paris (they are very large blocks), it's the best destination to stock up on bottled water and accessories. The Miracle Mile adjacent to Planet Hollywood has an ABC store which is affordable as well. Try to stay away from the hotel gift shops for water if you don't mind a 5-10 minute walk.My wife wanted to shop at the Premium outlets near downtown/ Fremont street. Rather than renting the most basic car for at least $50/day, we took a cab which was about $20 each way to the outlet. We later found out the some of The Deuce's routes, the double decker bus that runs up and down the strip, also goes up to Fremont street. For only $7 for a 24 hour pass, this is the way to go.If you work out, the gym in the hotel will cost you ~$20 a day (forgot the exact price); internet access within the room will cost you about $15. They'll get you for everything.Overall, we would stay at the Paris again; but I do wonder, what are the other hotels like?	
