 at every night. NIce wait staff and nice atmosphere. Drinks are expensive, but they are all over Vegas. Gamble a bit if you want a couple of free drinks! At the end of the trip, I asked to extend our check out, the man on the phone was SO nice and gave us an extra 2 hours! That was so kinds because we needed it after a 15 hour Grand Canyon bus trip the day before!!  Everyone is nice, helpful and willing to make your stay better!! Just ask!!!	
Aug 16 2009 	Not the same crowd as the Wynn	A week in Vegas, 4 days at the Wynn, 3 at Paris. Definately a different client then the Wynn. If you want to be entertained, meet middle America, and not break your bank in a half hour go to the Paris. Rooms are not large, but nice, beds are confortable. The table games range from $5+ during the day, $10+ in the evening. Major differences between the Wynn/Encore and Paris:1. If you want to pay for a beautiful room, reserved enviroment, good service go to the Wynn. If you want a nice room, good service,fun, lively, sometimes loud enviroment go to the Paris. LOL, don't know why, but at the Wynn someone beats the dealer in BJ, makes their point in craps or hits a big payout on slots, they just sit or stand there. No excitement. AT the Paris, someone hits anything that beats the house and everyone within site/sound cheers for them. 2. Both hotels had great service. The amazing thing was the Paris had 2-3 times the number of people playing/drinking and the service was excellent.3. If you want a nice, quite, relaxing/reserved enviroment that would be the Wynn/Encore. If you want a more intense, having fun crowd that would be the Paris.	
