Aug 13 2009	Perfect Location Perfect Rate.	We were traveling through on our way to California and needed a nice place to stay at a decent rate. Paris was a great deal for $69. It has a perfect location on center strip across from the Bellagio and Caesars Palace. Parking was easy enough with a large garage that was attached to the hotel. There is quite a bit of walking involved though from the parking garage though and dragging your luggage through the shops and casino just to get to the desk is a work out. The lobby is beautiful and check in was fairly easy even though there was a long line. The lady that checked us in was nice but a little preoccupied in closing out her shift. We had room 2087 on the 20th floor but had a view looking straight into rooms at Bally's. Elevators are quick and the hallways are quiet. The room was a decent size with some nice furniture, calm colors, large windows, and even a fully stocked mini bar, though quiet pricey. The bathroom was beautiful with it's separate shower and nice vanity. Quite large too. Wireless Internet costs $15 for 24 hours so I ended up bypassing that for the evening. The beds are comfortable but are not as comfortable as a pillow-top. Just a personal preference. The casino area is nice and has lots of great restaurants surrounding it and in she shopping area. Beautiful architecture adds to a nice ambiance. We only ate at one restaurant in Paris as it was the most economical for both breakfast and dinner; Ile St. Louis Cafe. Just like any restaurant in Vegas, quite pricey. $4.50 for a glass of orange juice? Though the prices for food in Vegas is rediculous, quality is never an issue. Very good food! The buffet always had a LONG line each time we walked by so we did not get to try it. As for shops, there are some interesting shops and neat bakeries, all with a neat French theme. The pool is on the third floor and has a great view of the strip. The pool is just a basic round pool with lots of seating. There are two nice hot tubs set in a garden area and plenty of towels are available. There's even food by the pool. I did get a chance to go up the Eiffel Tower for a beautiful view, but the weight was an hour and a half. I spent the extra $10 for the express option which gets you right up. Well worth it instead of waiting in line. Beautiful view!! Overall a great stay for the price though the food prices are horrible. Great location adds to the appeal for any Vegas traveler. I highly recommend it if you can get a cheap rate.	
