Jul 28 2009 	Loved it!	We go to Vegas every year; this has always been one of our favorite hotels overall. The buffet is our absolute favorite; the pastries and croissants are excellent. One of the best things about the hotel is that the casino is on one side and the shops and restaurants are on the other; the elevators are in the middle. So if you don't feel like walking through cigarette smoke while you shop and eat (but don't want a hotel that's so big you get lost) this is the place. It's a beautifully quaint hotel; rooms are a nice size with a sitting area, marble bathroom, separate shower and tub. We had a basic room and were very happy with it. Look for deals by going mid-week; it's much cheaper than weekends. In the morning the breakfast croissant is delicious, then get to the buffet before 3:30 for lunch pricing. This buffet is less expensive than many of the others. Rio's buffet is our close 2nd favorite. The Eiffel tower trip is a neat experience, go at night about 8 p.m. to avoid long lines and see the Bellagio fountains from a front row view. The pool and hot tubs were great, never overcrowded. Drink service was fast (which is surprising for pool service). We don't have any complaints. A solid 4 star hotel.	
