Jul 14 2009 	Location Location Location	We stayed at the Paris for 4 nights (July 8-11). I believe we were in what I have heard others refer to as a &quot;Red Room&quot;. The room was smallish, but very nicely decorated and clean. It included a King bed, small couch w/ coffee table, and a large storage armoire with a very large flat screen TV (not that we ever turned it on). The bathroom was nice with marble/tile. It had both tub for soaking and a shower. It was a little difficult for two people to get ready in front of the mirror at the same time, but not too bad. I would definitely recommend this place to others. Within this casino, we ate at the Eiffel Tower Restaurant (anniversary dinner $$$) and Mon Ami Gabi (breakfast $$). Both restaurants had excellent food. The Eiffel Tower Restaurant was a real treat. We made reservations ahead of time for our anniversary. They had dusted the table with rose petals and we had the best seat in the house, overlooking the Bellagio fountains. The wait staff were very attentive and our waiter offered to take our picture with personal camera several times. We ate chocolate/bacon waffles and French Toast with blueberries at Mon Ami Gabi. Both dishes were to die for! If you have never been to the strip, I can tell you this is where you want to stay, as it is centrally located. TIP: stop at a gas station on your way in and buy a case of water to keep in your room. It is much cheaper than buying bottles in the hotel convenience shops. It is extremely hot this time of year and you will need it to stay hydrated. Also, don't forget your lip balm and sunblock if you plan on doing alot of walking down the strip. Also, rewetting drops are essential for those of you who wear contacts. The sun and wind are fierce! If any of you out there are motorcyle riders, then I HIGHLY recommend a motorcycle tour with Todd Harbach of Vegas 2 Wheel Tours. We took a one day tour (8 hours) of REd Rock Canyon and Mount Charleston that was so AWESOME. He also treated us to a local summer theatre group at Spring Mountain Ranch, where we saw Westside Story, the night before our day tour. The show ended after dark, so our ride back to the trip was amazing. Nothing like riding under a full moon back into the lights of the Strip! This was by far the highlight of our Vegas trip. We fleyw in and rented a bike from Henderson Harley Davidson (discount rates for HOG members and Emergency personnel). You can Google both for tour/rental information.	
