d friendly during my learning curve.The best thing about Paris is the location. It's right in the middle of the Strip and easy to walk to the other hotels. We'll stay somewhere else when we go back, but only because that's part of the adventure to try out different hotels. I definitely recommend Paris.A few other notes of interest:Peepshow - take it or leave it ...&quot;O&quot; - finally saw it, it's excellent!Zefferino's at the Venetian - amazing foodDiablo's at Monte Carlo - fun atmosphere and good foodNathan Burton at Flamingo - fun time, appropriate for kids	
