ated lockers which is ridiculously inadequate for such a large hotel. The pool opens at 9 and we were there by 10 and they were all already in use. I did double check with the lifeguard and he said those were all that were available. They do provide an in-room safe but who wants to keep their wallet in the room and have to run up there if you want to buy a drink? My husband and I could not go in the pool at the same time as someone had to watch the wallets. Also, not one of the 3 sinks in the ladies' room worked. I saw two other ladies exit trying to get the soap off their hands. Overall, the hotel is really nice. The location is great! I am not sure I would stay there again due to the shower. But I would consider it as we liked the rest so much.	
