Apr 26 2009 	The Paris-Vegas	We travel to Vegas several times a year for business and pleasure. Sometimes we bring our kids (12, 9, 8) and sometimes not. We love the Paris in Vegas! It is a smaller casino, so it is easily and quickly get to places around the casino and hotel. It is located in the middle of the strip, so you have great access to other casinos-The Planet Hollywood (great sportsbooks, rockin' music, flat screen TVs everywhere). One of the best restaurants is in The Paris-Mon Ami Gabis. (I highly recommend the filet mignon with merlot butter sauce. And they have great French beer and wine.) There is a piano bar in the Paris, which is rockin' most nights. Lots of fun! We go there every time we are in Vegas. Sports bar is nice, usually has beer specials during big games. The Paris has an open stage in the casino, so live music is played on one side of the casino.The bad: The rooms are getting tired looking-not fabulous like other hotels on the strip. The pool does not get sun until noon, so the water is very cold (even in the summer). The drinks are way over-priced at the pool area. Cocktail waitresses at the open stage in the casino are never nice, so we have stopped going there.	
