Apr 25 2009 	Absolutely amazing time in Vegas and at Paris Hotel	I've now stayed at Paris for the 4th time...and have never stayed anyplace else. I went with my husband and his brother and sister met up with us a few days later. I was comped a room at the hotel and opted to pay $40 per night for a room with a view. Upon check in I asked if there were any suites and Amber (who was the nicest Front Reception employee I've ever dealt with) offered us a suite on the 33rd floor for only $85 per night (inclusive of the $40 previously mentioned)...so we took it and boy was it worth every penny. The suite was immaculate, the bathroom was stunning and we even received 2 rolloway beds at no charge. The service couldn't have been better. In all my stays at Paris, it has gotten better each time. I didn't see any signs of wear/tear and housekeeping was on top of things like you would not believe. I asked for extra towels, blankets and sheets and they were delivered right away. Mints were left on our pillow each night and the room was spotless when we returned in the afternoon.Everyone we encountered were very nice and helpful. We ate dinner at the burger place which was fantastic and also at Mon Ami Gabi. That is a restaurant everyone should try when they are in Vegas (whether you stay at Paris or not). The steaks were out of this world. One could easily find negative things to point out if they really wanted to but I guess my attitude is that you are on vacation and unless something is REALLY wrong, then let is go and try to have a good time. The shower pressure wasn't the best, the sink in the mini bar didn't drain all that well but I didn't stress but instead took a few extra minutes to take a shower - I mean, what's the big deal. You are on vacation. It would take me no time at all to consider returning to Paris. We had such a great time and until I have a reason not to, I see no purpose in trying out any other hotel. Where else can you get such a great location, a beautiful hotel, great places to eat and terrific deals. It was all good.	
