Apr 16 2009 	Awesome Location with the most detail	It was a beauty of a hotel and casino - literally transporting us to Paris with the cobblestone(like) streets and faux storefronts and painted ceilings, replicated eiffel tower etc... . It was centrally located on the strip so easy to go in either direction. Helpful staff and good wait service in the casino. Gambling not so great - not too much of a run for your money on the slots and tables were all a $10 minimum (a bit much for our taste were hoping for a $5). The hotel itself was very nice, they gouged us at check in claiming that there were no smoking rooms available even though that was requsted at the time of booking and verified 3 days before hand so they graciously offered us an upgraded smoking room on the 27th floor with a good view that we would be pleased with (had requested a view of the Bellagio fountains) for a mere $40 more a night. We only paid $60 to begin with so being eager to start our vacation we agreed. The room was beautiful, one of the newly remodeled Red Rooms - yes it was on the 27th floor which offered a georgeous view of the back of Bally's outdated hotel. Was not pleased with the view but whatever you don't spend much time in the room anyway. The bathroom was beautiful it was all very clean and well kept. Easy video check out and ability to check your bill on the tv screen - good thing because they had charged us several mini bar charges that we had not even used. Come to find out that the mini bar is hooked up to sensors and if you move anything out it charges you - well we had a few things we needed to have kept cold so moved things around and set them other places hence the charges, they were taken off when we called the front desk to dispute. Overall a good experience - learned a few lessons in the process but a very nice hotel.	
