Mar 23 2009 	Have Loved Paris for 4 years! : )	We have only stayed at the Paris and the Luxor. Paris is the only place we will stay. Have received offers that include free rooms at Ceasar's this year, but we're happy at Paris and rooms at Ceasar's don't seem that much better, and require more play to maintain same level of offers.Our first trip to Vegas we stayed at the Luxor. We just stopped into the Paris as we were walking the strip. We registered at the Players Club desk and played VERY briefly.We started getting offers within a couple of weeks and they were much better than the offers we got from the Luxor properties. We signed up for a Bally's slot tournament and stayed at Paris for free. Got an upgrade to a Concierge room for $60 night, but had problems with the tub so room was comped.We won $100 in the slot tournament, what fun. : )Luxury and Premium rooms are not huge but we like them alot. We always get a room with a view of the Eiffel Tower and Bellagio fountains. That also comes with a mini bar upgrade.We usually have enough comps to cover a room upgrade, (if we are charged for it up front), mini bar, a meal and some items from the gift shop.We bring a bank roll of $300 per day for two of us, so we are not high rollers.Last time we won $1,000 twice on the same slot machine. This paid for our whole bank roll for the whole trip! We have broken even once, and come home with a couple hundred of our original bank roll twice, and then last time came home with $2,000. So we are VERY happy with the gambling at Paris.Service when we had a problem was slow, but we really like the waitresses in the casino and everyone else has been every nice. We like to have our first meal at Mon Ami Gabi and the staff is always great. Housekeeping is SUPER friendly and helpful.Only criticism is that there are no cofffeemakers in-room (but this is common for all strip hotels) and the breakfast selections are not great. We usually like a big breakfast and then don't eat again until dinner. I think there is a breakfast buffet now, so I am looking forward to trying that during our trip in May.May trip includes room, slot tournament, brunch and awards buffet comped. : )Where else can you go with an expectation of having things paid for at the end of your trip and possibly having part or all or MORE of your original expenses paid? Gotta love Vegas.	
Mar 23 2009 	Could have done much better!	Check in was okay. The room was okay. I would not necessarily stay here again. It is far to expensive. I could never bring my family here. We paid $40 for breakfast for two. We had a COD food line at our training and a banana was $3.50 as was a cup of coffee. The room amenities were well, there were none, unless you consider $4 for a candy bar and $10 for gummy bears an amenitiy. Thanks anyway but next time I will go back to Ceasers Palace, now that was awesome. By the way it is $15 a day to have internet access. You have to be kidding!	
Mar 22 2009 	e.g. Liked the central location	OUTSTANDING! We stayed at Paris last October and enjoyed every minute of it. The check-in was fast and very courteous. When we opened the door to our room we were thrilled with the French Provincial decor. The location of all Harrah's properties in this area of the strip is exceptional. The pool is nice, the food is great and we were able to win some play money on the slots. We are returning to Las Vegas in April and Paris is the hotel of our choice.	
